commentary: Henry to Bairstow, 2 runs juggle, juggle and Santner drops it. He is down on his knees. Banged in short and rises outside off, Bairstow ramps it in the air, the ball hits his palm, then his chest and he grasses it. He tries to snatch it on the third attempt but it proves futile. He pedalled back and then belatedly went forward. Santner misjudged it at deep third man
